02:05.800 --> 02:08.326
RIGGAN AS BIRDMAN: <i>How
did we end up here?</i>

02:14.360 --> 02:16.362
<i>This place is horrible.</i>

02:22.000 --> 02:24.207
<i>Smells like balls.</i>

02:30.200 --> 02:32.407
<i>We don't belong in this shithole.</i>

02:32.480 --> 02:35.051
- (LAPTOP CHIMING)
- (RIGGAN EXHALES DEEPLY)

02:38.880 --> 02:40.166
(CRACKING)

02:46.360 --> 02:47.566
RIGGAN: Shit.

02:51.880 --> 02:52.881
Hey, Sam.

02:53.040 --> 02:54.724
<i>Dad, what kind of--
Shut up!</i>

02:54.920 --> 02:56.410
<i>What kind of flowers did you want?</i>

02:56.600 --> 02:59.410
Alchemillas.
Or something that smells nice.

02:59.600 --> 03:02.604
- Something soothing.
- <i>It all smells like fucking kimchi!</i>

03:02.880 --> 03:05.724
That looks nice.
Anything but roses.

03:05.920 --> 03:07.604
<i>I hate this job.</i>

03:07.680 --> 03:09.091
(CHIMING)

03:09.440 --> 03:10.771
(SIGHS)

03:17.320 --> 03:18.924
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

03:20.120 --> 03:21.610
(INHALES DEEPLY)

03:29.240 --> 03:30.765
ANNIE: (OVER SPEAKER)
<i>Riggan, everyone's set for 1-4.</i>

03:30.840 --> 03:32.251
<i>They're ready for you.</i>

03:34.080 --> 03:36.082
<i>Riggan, they're ready for you.</i>

03:36.640 --> 03:37.880
(EXHALES)

03:53.600 --> 03:55.523
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

04:08.920 --> 04:10.410
- Mr. Thomson.
- Steve.

04:10.680 --> 04:12.682
- It's Daniel.
- Okay.

04:15.600 --> 04:17.442
JAKE: Oh, hey, buddy.
How you doing?

04:17.680 --> 04:21.082
Pretty good. Yeah, I'd be a lot
better if I could get, uh...

04:21.360 --> 04:23.362
...Ralph to stop, you know, acting.

04:23.600 --> 04:24.681
He'll be fine.

04:24.920 --> 04:28.003
And he was yelling, "I love
you, I love you, bitch!"

04:28.120 --> 04:29.929
- (SCOFFS)
- What do you do with a love like that?

04:30.280 --> 04:32.647
That's not love and you know it.

04:32.720 --> 04:33.767
Why do you insist on calling it love?

04:34.040 --> 04:36.771
Say what you want,
but I know what it was.

04:37.040 --> 04:39.520
What about you, Nick?
Does that sound like love?

04:39.800 --> 04:41.609
Sorry I'm late.
Sound like love...

04:41.880 --> 04:43.120
Look, I'm the wrong person to ask.

04:43.200 --> 04:46.363
I only heard the man's name
mentioned in passing.

04:46.640 --> 04:48.449
I wouldn't know.
You'd have to know the particulars.

04:48.520 --> 04:51.126
I think you're saying
love is absolute.

04:51.440 --> 04:53.807
Yeah. The kind of love
I'm talking about is...

04:54.040 --> 04:55.530
The kind of love I'm talking about,

04:55.600 --> 04:56.886
you don't try and kill people.

04:57.120 --> 04:59.009
It was love, Mel.
To Eddie, it was.

04:59.080 --> 05:00.730
I don't care what anyone says.

05:00.800 --> 05:01.961
He was ready to die for it.

05:02.200 --> 05:04.806
- Ask her what he did after she left him.
- (SIGHS)

05:05.120 --> 05:07.521
He shot himself in the mouth,
but he screwed that up, too.

05:07.600 --> 05:08.726
Poor Ed.

05:08.960 --> 05:11.804
Poor Ed, my ass!
The guy was dangerous!

05:12.080 --> 05:14.401
LAURA: How did he screw
up shooting himself in the mouth?

05:14.640 --> 05:17.325
He used to carry this. 22.
We lived like fugitives then.

05:17.640 --> 05:19.005
Ralph, Ralph, Ralph.

05:19.320 --> 05:20.845
Fugitives are scared, you know?

05:20.920 --> 05:24.163
Fugitives are on the run.

05:24.480 --> 05:26.847
Can you give me more of that?
You know, fear?

05:27.080 --> 05:28.411
RALPH: Great idea.

05:29.160 --> 05:31.003
We lived like fugitives then.

05:31.320 --> 05:33.891
I never knew if he was going
to come out from behind a bush,

05:33.960 --> 05:35.689
or a car, and just start shooting.

05:35.920 --> 05:39.083
The man was crazy!
He was capable of anything!

05:39.440 --> 05:41.090
LAURA: Christ, what a nightmare.

05:41.360 --> 05:43.169
He'd call me at the hospital and say:

05:43.520 --> 05:47.206
"Son of a bitch,
your days are numbered!"

05:49.360 --> 05:51.488
Too much?
It's a little bit too much.

05:51.560 --> 05:54.040
I can tell, because you--
I just want to give you a range.

05:55.760 --> 05:57.205
JAKE: Call 911!

05:57.520 --> 05:58.851
LESLEY: Is he breathing?

05:59.120 --> 06:01.122
LAURA: Is blood coming out of his ear?

06:01.360 --> 06:02.361
Where are you going?

06:02.600 --> 06:03.647
LAURA: Did someone call 911?

06:03.720 --> 06:05.961
JAKE: Do not move him!
Wait for an ambulance!

06:06.200 --> 06:08.043
Well, that's a fucking lawsuit.

06:08.280 --> 06:10.282
Where are you going?
The understudy'll be here.

06:10.520 --> 06:12.727
Forget the understudy.
Cancel the first preview.

06:12.960 --> 06:14.883
But it's a full house!
We'd have to refund--

06:14.960 --> 06:16.371
Just do it.

06:17.040 --> 06:18.201
- How's Ralph?
- He'll be fine.

06:18.480 --> 06:20.130
Wait. Will you fucking wait?

06:20.400 --> 06:22.050
Jake, it would have been a disaster.

06:22.120 --> 06:23.724
That guy's the worst
actor I've ever seen.

06:24.040 --> 06:26.042
Bleeding's the most honest
thing he's done so far.

06:26.320 --> 06:28.322
He's not that bad!

06:29.720 --> 06:31.404
Okay, he's fucking terrible.

06:31.720 --> 06:34.883
You have the press in your dressing
room in a few hours.

06:35.160 --> 06:37.242
I'll make something up.
I'll think of something, riff.

06:37.320 --> 06:38.446
Hold on.

06:40.240 --> 06:42.242
That wasn't an accident.

06:44.160 --> 06:45.321
What do you mean?

06:45.560 --> 06:47.244
I made it happen.

06:47.560 --> 06:48.925
Oh, okay.

06:49.240 --> 06:50.571
Are you drunk?

06:50.920 --> 06:54.083
Just find me an actor-- a good actor.
Woody Harrelson!

06:54.400 --> 06:55.925
He's doing the next <i>Hunger Games.</i>

06:56.160 --> 06:57.321
Um, Michael Fassbender.

06:57.600 --> 06:59.409
He's doing the prequel
to the <i>X-Men</i> prequel.

06:59.680 --> 07:01.682
- How about, uh, Jeremy Renner?
- Who?

07:01.920 --> 07:05.925
Jeremy Renner! He was nominated.
The <i>Hurt Locker</i> guy.

07:06.160 --> 07:07.605
He's an Avenger.

07:07.840 --> 07:11.686
Fuck! They put him in a cape, too?
I don't care.

07:11.920 --> 07:13.445
Just find me someone.

07:14.760 --> 07:18.287
Ralph will sue us.
He will sue us and he has a case.

07:21.280 --> 07:22.611
Just make it go away.

07:22.960 --> 07:27.602
Look, you're my attorney. You're my
producer. You're my best friend.

07:27.880 --> 07:31.202
Now go out there and do
what you were born to do.

07:31.440 --> 07:33.647
How do you suppose I do that?
How--

07:35.960 --> 07:39.282
NEWSREADER: (ON TV) <i>Next, an exclusive
interview with Robert Downey, Jr...</i>

07:39.560 --> 07:42.882
<i>...who's busy following up his
billion-dollar </i> Iron Man <i> franchise...</i>

07:43.120 --> 07:46.966
<i>...with the equally successful
</i> Avengers <i> series.</i>

07:47.080 --> 07:48.684
(CLICKS)

07:54.160 --> 07:55.366
(SIGHS)

07:55.960 --> 07:58.486
BIRDMAN: <i>That clown doesn't
have half your talent...</i>

07:58.720 --> 08:02.725
<i>...and he's making a fortune
in that </i> Tin Man <i> get-up.</i>

08:02.800 --> 08:03.926
(SIGHS)

08:04.000 --> 08:06.321
<i>We were the real thing, Riggan.</i>

08:08.000 --> 08:09.650
- <i>We had it all.</i>
- (INHALES DEEPLY)

08:10.320 --> 08:12.163
- <i>We gave it away.</i>
- (EXHALES)

08:12.480 --> 08:13.845
Breathing in.

08:14.320 --> 08:17.164
<i>We handed these poseurs
the keys to the kingdom.</i>

08:17.400 --> 08:18.606
Breathing out.

08:18.840 --> 08:20.330
<i>You listening to me?</i>

08:21.320 --> 08:22.560
Breathing in, I embrace my anger.

08:22.640 --> 08:23.687
(BIRDMAN LAUGHING)

08:24.000 --> 08:26.002
<i>Yeah, embrace it.</i>

08:26.240 --> 08:29.369
<i>But I'm not going away.
You know I'm right.</i>

08:35.600 --> 08:36.681
(GRUNTS)

08:57.360 --> 08:59.044
<i>Look at that.</i>

09:00.560 --> 09:03.882
<i>These people don't know
what you're capable of.</i>

09:04.360 --> 09:05.725
(SHATTERS)

09:10.040 --> 09:12.646
GABRIEL: Why would somebody
go from playing

09:12.720 --> 09:15.041
the lead in a comic
book franchise...

09:15.400 --> 09:19.564
...to adapting Raymond Carver
for the stage? (SIGHS)

09:20.080 --> 09:23.084
As you're probably aware,
Barthes said:

09:23.320 --> 09:27.803
"The cultural work done
in the past by gods and epic sagas..."

09:28.080 --> 09:31.721
"...is now being done by laundry
detergent commercials..."

09:32.080 --> 09:34.401
"...and comic strip characters."

09:35.000 --> 09:36.843
This is a big leap you've taken.

09:37.080 --> 09:40.084
Yeah, it is.
Absolutely. Absolutely.

09:40.400 --> 09:42.402
(CLEARS THROAT)
Like you said...

09:42.760 --> 09:45.650
...that, uh, Barthes said, uh...

09:46.080 --> 09:47.241
Birdman, like Icarus--

09:47.520 --> 09:50.046
Okay, hang on.
Who is this Barthes guy?

09:50.120 --> 09:51.451
Which <i>Birdman</i> was he in?

09:51.680 --> 09:54.411
GABRIEL: Uh, Roland Barthes
was a French philosopher,

09:54.480 --> 09:56.687
and if you knew anything
about the history of--

09:56.920 --> 10:00.925
Now is it true you've been injecting
yourself with semen from baby pigs?

10:01.440 --> 10:03.761
- I'm sorry, what?
- As a method of facial rejuvenation?

10:04.120 --> 10:05.201
Where did you read that?

10:05.440 --> 10:08.444
It was tweeted
by @prostatewhispers.

10:08.760 --> 10:09.921
(CHUCKLES)
That's not true.

10:10.000 --> 10:11.047
I know, but did you do it?

10:11.280 --> 10:12.281
No, I didn't do it.

10:12.360 --> 10:13.691
Okay, I'll write you're denying it.

10:13.960 --> 10:17.123
Don't write anything.
Why would you write anything?

10:17.440 --> 10:20.967
Don't write what she said.
I didn't put any baby pig...

10:21.280 --> 10:24.966
GABRIEL: Are you at all afraid that people
will say you're doing this play...

10:25.200 --> 10:28.124
...to battle the impression
you're a washed-up superhero?

10:28.360 --> 10:30.408
No, absolutely not.
That's why...

10:30.640 --> 10:34.486
- ...twenty years ago, I said no to <i>Birdman 4.</i>
- (HAN GASPING)

10:35.800 --> 10:38.485
<i>Birdman 4?</i> You do <i>Birdman 4?!</i>

10:38.800 --> 10:41.167
Thank you for coming out.
Thank you.

10:41.240 --> 10:43.163
We're expecting some great pieces.

10:43.480 --> 10:46.643
(SIGHS)
The guys in publicity...

10:47.160 --> 10:49.162
want a <i>Times</i> feature,

10:49.240 --> 10:51.811
which is the worst idea right now.

10:52.320 --> 10:53.560
(SIGHS)

10:55.400 --> 10:56.561
What are you doing?

10:56.640 --> 10:57.766
I don't want to look at this anymore.

10:58.000 --> 10:59.490
That was a present from the crew.

10:59.560 --> 11:01.005
Don't fuck with them--
they're union.

11:01.320 --> 11:02.685
I don't care.

11:03.320 --> 11:05.402
- How'd it go?
- Good.

11:05.680 --> 11:07.364
They talk about Ralph?
He did it.

11:07.440 --> 11:08.851
The motherfucker did it.

11:09.080 --> 11:11.082
Threatened to sue us.

11:11.320 --> 11:12.845
- What'd you say?
- Me?

11:13.080 --> 11:15.606
I said, "Motherfucker,
are you threatening me?"

11:15.680 --> 11:17.762
"If I so much as get
a letter from a lawyer..."

11:18.000 --> 11:20.685
"...the press is getting
pictures off your computer."

11:20.920 --> 11:22.081
What pictures?

11:22.360 --> 11:25.364
He has a thing for nuns in diapers.

11:25.680 --> 11:29.526
Why do you care?
Point is, I made it go away.

11:29.840 --> 11:31.205
That's great.

11:31.440 --> 11:33.886
Yeah, it's fantastic,
except for one thing.

11:34.200 --> 11:35.770
- We have no actor.
- Uh-huh.

11:35.880 --> 11:38.201
And if we cancel the preview,
the press will smell blood.

11:38.520 --> 11:40.727
We can't afford to lose
any more money.

11:40.960 --> 11:42.291
What do you think I should do?

11:42.520 --> 11:43.885
We hired an understudy.

11:43.960 --> 11:45.200
- Use him.
- No.

11:45.440 --> 11:48.569
Riggan, listen to me.
Please, for the love of God, listen.

11:48.880 --> 11:51.326
Our perfect dream actor is not going
to knock on that door and go,

11:51.480 --> 11:53.562
- "Hey, fellas, when do I start?"
- (KNOCKING ON DOOR)

11:55.560 --> 11:57.403
- Can I talk to you?
- What's up?

11:57.640 --> 11:59.722
- You find another actor?
- No.

12:00.480 --> 12:01.970
- Mike's available.
- Mike who?

12:02.240 --> 12:03.446
I thought he was doing the thing--

12:03.520 --> 12:05.249
He quit. Or got fired.

12:05.320 --> 12:06.321
Mike who?

12:06.400 --> 12:08.402
- Which is it, quit or fired?
- With Mike, it's usually both.

12:08.640 --> 12:10.324
- Mike fucking who?
- Shiner.

12:10.560 --> 12:11.891
- Yes!
- Jake.

12:12.160 --> 12:13.924
How do you know Mike Shiner?

12:14.000 --> 12:15.240
We share a vagina.

12:15.480 --> 12:16.481
- You think he'd do it?
- Mmm-hmm.

12:16.720 --> 12:18.484
- How do you know?
- He told me.

12:18.720 --> 12:20.131
- Jake.
- Yes.

12:20.200 --> 12:22.089
Ask me if he sells tickets.

12:22.320 --> 12:23.401
Does he sell tickets?

12:23.480 --> 12:26.324
A shitload. Ask me if the
theater critics love him.

12:26.560 --> 12:27.800
Do theater critics love him?

12:27.880 --> 12:30.247
They want to spooge on him.

12:30.600 --> 12:32.409
- Right on his face.
- Everything for a reason.

12:32.760 --> 12:33.921
You think he'd come in this evening?

12:34.000 --> 12:35.809
I'll call and find out.

12:36.120 --> 12:37.485
I'll call his agent.

12:38.160 --> 12:39.161
Amazing, amazing.

12:47.640 --> 12:50.644
Annie? Clear the theater,
send everyone to dinner

12:50.720 --> 12:52.643
and give me some lights!

12:53.040 --> 12:54.201
We've got a put-in tonight.

12:54.280 --> 12:55.361
ANNIE: Who?

12:55.640 --> 12:57.005
JAKE: You'll find out.

13:10.160 --> 13:11.844
Intimidating, isn't it?

13:12.320 --> 13:13.890
You have any idea the people who have

13:13.960 --> 13:17.009
walked on these boards before you?

13:17.680 --> 13:20.160
Geraldine Page. Helen Hayes.

13:20.520 --> 13:24.491
Jason Robards. Marlon Brando.
And now Riggan Thomson.

13:24.960 --> 13:27.804
(CHUCKLES) Thanks for coming
in on such short notice, Mike.

13:28.160 --> 13:29.491
This is what I do.

13:29.560 --> 13:31.164
You wrote this adaptation?

13:31.400 --> 13:32.561
- I did, yeah.
- Ah.

13:32.800 --> 13:36.009
And you're directing and starring.
That's ambitious.

13:36.320 --> 13:37.321
Well, thanks.

13:37.640 --> 13:40.007
Well, it's a good theater.

13:40.640 --> 13:44.167
I can't speak for your play, but...
let's do a little bit of it.

13:44.480 --> 13:46.562
RIGGAN: Oh, I didn't expect
you to just jump right in.

13:46.840 --> 13:49.320
It's first preview tomorrow night.
Let's get to work.

13:49.560 --> 13:53.406
Well, feel free to take the script
up until you feel comfortable.

13:53.680 --> 13:56.160
No, let's just do some of it.

13:57.520 --> 13:58.521
Uh...

13:58.600 --> 13:59.931
Take a look at page 20.

14:00.160 --> 14:01.685
I'm good. I don't need it.

14:01.920 --> 14:03.126
I don't need the script.
Give me a cue.

14:03.200 --> 14:04.361
What?

14:04.600 --> 14:06.284
- Feed me a line.
- (STAMMERING)

14:06.520 --> 14:07.681
Feed me a line.

14:07.760 --> 14:08.841
Okay.

14:09.200 --> 14:11.362
Okay, uh, let me think.

14:13.680 --> 14:16.524
I'm the wrong person to ask.
I didn't actually know him.

14:16.640 --> 14:18.961
- I only heard his name mentioned in passing.
- Mmm-hmm.

14:19.040 --> 14:20.644
You'd have to know
the particulars.

14:20.760 --> 14:24.048
But I think what you're
saying is love is absolute.

14:24.880 --> 14:28.282
Is that what I'm saying? Am I saying
love is absolute? (INHALES SHARPLY)

14:28.360 --> 14:30.203
Yes. Okay, yeah!
The kind of love

14:30.280 --> 14:31.884
I'm talking about is absolute.

14:32.200 --> 14:35.886
The kind of love I'm talking about,
you don't try to kill people!

14:36.120 --> 14:37.804
How do you know the lines?

14:38.360 --> 14:40.508
It's a thing I have.
I don't know, it's a gift.

14:40.534 --> 14:41.070
Wow.

14:42.400 --> 14:45.404
Come on. I've been helping
Lesley get off book for a month.

14:45.640 --> 14:48.041
- These lines are right here.
- That makes sense.

14:48.400 --> 14:49.970
That's good.
Give me my cue again.

14:50.240 --> 14:52.720
I'm the wrong person to ask.
I didn't actually know him.

14:52.960 --> 14:55.725
I only heard his name
mentioned in passing.

14:55.960 --> 14:58.406
You never know the particulars.
I think what--

14:58.640 --> 15:00.483
Can I make a suggestion?

15:00.560 --> 15:02.244
- Do you mind?
- No, not at all.

15:02.560 --> 15:06.087
No, no, forget that.
Just stay with me.

15:06.400 --> 15:10.086
"I'm the wrong person to ask,"
he says, but what's the intention?

15:10.320 --> 15:12.243
Is he fed up with the subject?

15:12.320 --> 15:14.004
Deflecting guilt over the marriage?

15:14.240 --> 15:16.447
And here's the thing--
you have four lines after that

15:16.560 --> 15:19.245
that all say the same thing.
"I didn't know him."

15:19.600 --> 15:21.807
"I only heard his name
mentioned in passing."

15:21.880 --> 15:23.086
"I wouldn't know."

15:23.320 --> 15:24.765
"You'd have to know
the particulars."

15:24.840 --> 15:27.002
"Particulars" sounds like my grandmother.

15:27.280 --> 15:30.921
The point is, you don't know the guy.
We fucking get it.

15:31.280 --> 15:32.611
Make it work with one line.

15:32.680 --> 15:34.762
"I didn't even know the man." Right?

15:35.120 --> 15:37.930
Wait-- You know my lines, too, huh?

15:38.280 --> 15:40.442
Can we not get hung up on knowing lines?

15:40.520 --> 15:42.602
Can we just work on this?
Tear it apart?

15:42.840 --> 15:45.127
So why don't you just give
me that same thing again,

15:45.200 --> 15:47.362
- but cut it down. Try it.
- Uh...

15:47.600 --> 15:48.965
I'm the wrong person to ask--

15:49.200 --> 15:52.124
Oh, no! That's the thing--
"I'm the wrong person to ask."

15:52.200 --> 15:53.201
I think it's, "Fuck you."

15:53.440 --> 15:55.807
"Fuck you. Don't put me on the spot."

15:56.040 --> 15:58.805
"Don't make me feel
self-conscious about my marriage"

15:58.880 --> 16:00.882
"while my wife is sitting..."

16:01.120 --> 16:02.804
- Right there.
- "...right there."

16:03.120 --> 16:05.487
- Can I sit down for this?
- Yeah, sit. Good idea.

16:05.800 --> 16:09.327
So just give it to me
as a "Fuck you." Lay it on me.

16:09.640 --> 16:10.971
Just do it. Give it to me.

16:11.240 --> 16:13.561
- Well, I'm thinking.
- Fuck me hard. Just give it.

16:13.800 --> 16:14.801
Come on! Just do it!

16:15.040 --> 16:17.088
Hey, I'm the wrong
person to ask!

